The paper deals with the problem of learning the structure of multivariate linear tree models, which is a topic that falls under the broad area of machine learning. The proposed algorithm is based on spectral methods, which are commonly used in machine learning and signal processing. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with latent variables, which are a common topic in artificial intelligence, so cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely. The problem of learning tree structures is related to graph theory and algorithms, so cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possible sub-category. The paper also discusses sample complexity and statistical properties, which are topics in information theory (cs.IT) and statistics (cs.SI).
